@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #89295 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
left a note because I cant reproduce
This issue still has I-prioritize but hasn't had any activity since September. What should we do?
I suggest we ask people if they've had other instances of it reoccurring. If it's a one-off fluke, maybe we should just close?

The project should really have some guidelines on what to do with old errors that can't be reproduced. Most projects would close if that was the case, but since we don't have any guidelines, the reports tend to just float there.

this issue was hard for me to pinpoint because lacking of a manageable codebase to try a reproducible

last comment mentioned that it reproduces on their CI. Now most of their CI jobs are green
https://github.com/subspace/subspace/actions

... so, well, problem solved? :)
